
    THE ANC in Eastern Cape has called for tough action against people implicated in the Public Protector’s report on government’s expenditure on the funeral of the late former president, Nelson Mandela. Madiba died on 5 December 2013 and his funeral was held at his rural home, Qunu outside Mthatha.  ANC provincial secretary Lulama Ngcukayitobi has called on Premier Phumulo Masualle and all relevant government agencies, such as the Hawks and National Prosecuting Authority, to take action on the findings by Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane.  if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsuyVKvRGNjZkdWeK13IPwoq2rgU-EoAK7i_VDHCvs688W5-sOZbSTAqZt5uFQ198T9pDkP4Ufdrsbd8J8qdBHysRdhNp_kLl1SJstkYyhUfKrfVr4IXB_ljmkuS84loOGk1TpIZZuqBv20cPpYTKxC-MAtqYr9pTKfINnX1tTmGyGy5-3wskyWkcEtq59M3-i0Bfyojw1ORvkud0l0PMxHnk4qA-TiSsgtIKlH0mjPTyvlG9GFwG4M6-I2l5f69t3pC2amGyuGVOnvK1uSEpwxjQgj1hBU\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzJOwGFEy-0oGEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
